Reasoning: The paper deals with domain adaptation, which is a common problem in machine learning and falls under the category of "Learning" (cs.LG). The paper specifically focuses on the problem of blending target domain adaptation, which involves multiple sub-targets, and proposes a novel approach to address this problem. This suggests that the paper could also be relevant to the sub-categories of "Computer Vision" (cs.CV) and "Artificial Intelligence" (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of unsupervised meta-learning, which falls under the sub-category of "Natural Language Processing" (cs.CL) and the evaluation of the proposed approach on three benchmarks, which suggests that the paper could also be relevant to the sub-category of "Multimedia" (cs.MM).
